For each pair of host and virus proteins, we represent the relative frequency of amino acid triplets (RFAT) as a feature vector with 686 elements (343 for a host protein and 343 for a virus protein). The RFAT of the i-th amino acid triplet is defined by Eq. 1. In the equation, fi, avgF, and maxF denote the frequency of the i-th amino acid triplet, the average, and the maximum frequency of amino acid triplets in the protein sequence, respectively. 
