Another feature is the frequency difference of amino acid triplets (FDAT) between virus and host proteins, which is defined by Eq. 2. In Eq. 2, fhi is the frequency of the i-th amino acid triplet in the host protein of the host-virus pair, and fvi is the frequency of the i-th amino acid triplet in the virus protein of the same host-virus pair. avgFD and maxFD denote the average and the maximum frequency difference of amino acid triplets in a host-virus pair, respectively. 
